Welcome to Scoutzknivez_Vantagepoint :) This is my first final release map! The gameplay for this map is quite different from regular sk. Normal sk has an emphasis on simplicity by which people are immediately confronted with enemy fire when they walked out the door. In this sense their is a focus on reflex, aim, strafing ability and experience. For this map, i placed an emphasis,more so, on strategy and tactics through the implementation of a variety of vantage points and routes. By increasing the number of routes through the map, the player may ambush an enemy rather than having to have a direct shoot off until one dies like in normal sk. In this sense, sk_vantagepoint is different from normal sk. I have also increased the amount of indoor areas. However, i also increased the view points to these areas to prevent excessive camping. Needless to say this map definitely follows the saying "the more the marrier" as it allows varies different strategic offensives and defensives for either team. I really hope you enjoy this map and are able to play it under its full capacity with 16 or so people and a decent knowledge of the map. This way you will be able to execute effective offensives/defensives by taking the numerous routes throughout the map and have a lot of fun doing it. Troy :) xD =P

I was thinking one day.. Hey, scoutz has low gravity usually right? So why has no one made a map of scoutz in outerspace? Well I decided to do just that.

Features:

- Three comets that revolve around the arena
- The arena is located on a comet
- Air vents that push you upwards
- Nice skybox
- Removed the spawns near the doors that let people shoot someone right when the round begins
- Kept the small filesize (2.53 MB)
- Included a res file for the banner, all you have to do is edit the res to make your banner show instead
- Skybox texture packed in the BSP so you don't have to worry about a RES file for that

Credits:

BadMofo and Mitchard for supporting me and uploading the map to our server :D

TREXiL for testing it out for me and taking numerous screenshots! Big thanks to you buddy.

My video card is shot right now, so if you find any bugs report them to me please, and suggestions are ALWAYS welcome!

This is one of my first released maps, though I've been mapping for ages.

Scoutzknivez Nextgen is another take on the Scoutzknives style. Generally, these kinds of maps have a singular way of playing. Usually, it's left vs. right, put some objects in the middle. I tried to mix that up here. Instead of the usual 1 level, this map has 3 levels of insaneness. This makes for some very interresting and unpredictable gameplay that's sure to satisfy the hardcore gamers.
All players start out with a scout and a knife-- obviously, but also 2 grenades incase they want to be... tactical. This was a gimmick that was inserted in an early version where gameplay was centered on 2 specific chokepoints. I decided to leave it in because it added deeper gameplay, without messing balance up too much.

As said though, this is one of my first maps. I'm looking for feedback on what I did right, and what I did wrong, so that I can improve.

Anyways, the dev texture style is obviously intentional, my next map will be less arcadish and will resemble real life more. Or said in another way, it won't have dev textures. I tried to give this map a bit more professional look than most Dev maps though, mainly by adding HDR, a Skybox and some generally interresting geometry.

This is the first and only version of the map, unless something really major means I have to fix something. So post away!

File size is 4.3 mb, which is quite small for a map, but quite big for a map this size. Blame HDR. Anyways, when B2Z packed, it should download real quick anyways.
Maximum players is 28

Recommended settings:
SV_gravity should be 140
SV_Airaccelerate should be 100 or above

,-Dr.SharK
